19
00:01:41,029 --> 00:01:43,600
[Episode 10]

20
00:01:49,110 --> 00:01:51,790
What do we do if Director Lin still doesn't agree to it?

21
00:01:51,790 --> 00:01:54,829
No ifs. There's no turning back for Huateng Land.

22
00:01:56,830 --> 00:01:58,650
- Director Lin.
- Director Lin.

23
00:01:58,650 --> 00:02:00,270
Have a seat.

24
00:02:05,730 --> 00:02:08,919
Director Lin. We're so sorry for missing the appointment.

25
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:13,750
Besides asking you to give Huateng Land another chance,

26
00:02:13,750 --> 00:02:16,360
we came to apologize to you in person as well.

27
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:21,199
If you're here for Qinghu, I suggest you don't waste your time.

28
00:02:21,199 --> 00:02:23,899
I know that Wancheng hasn't decided on the final business partner.

29
00:02:23,899 --> 00:02:28,659
Could you give us another chance since Qinghu holds a special meaning to you?

30
00:02:28,659 --> 00:02:32,180
At least, do take a look at our latest proposal.

31
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:36,640
Tell me then. How is it that Qinghu is of great significance to me?

32
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:41,219
As far as I know, Qinghu was where you worked during the Down to the Countryside Movement in the late '70s.

33
00:02:41,219 --> 00:02:43,259
You stayed there for five years.

34
00:02:43,259 --> 00:02:46,139
Later on, you established Wancheng and devoted yourself to the real estate industry.

35
00:02:46,139 --> 00:02:48,220
Then, you began to prepare for the Impression Qinghu project.

36
00:02:48,220 --> 00:02:52,339
So far, it should have been nearly ten years now.

37
00:02:52,339 --> 00:02:56,440
This is the project that you invested the longest time in since you established Wancheng.

38
00:02:58,220 --> 00:02:59,939
Young lady.

39
00:02:59,939 --> 00:03:03,620
Don't act as if you know me well after reading a few online news articles about me.

40
00:03:03,620 --> 00:03:08,039
On the contrary, I'm disgusted with this place, Qinghu.

41
00:03:08,039 --> 00:03:11,759
To me, it doesn't matter who wins the tender or what the inside story is.

42
00:03:11,759 --> 00:03:14,919
As long as Wancheng doesn't lose money, it's the same no matter who gets the tender.

43
00:03:14,919 --> 00:03:17,740
But after all, Qinghu is where your career started.

44
00:03:17,740 --> 00:03:21,700
I don't believe you'll choose to work with a partner of bad character.

45
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:29,800
For the things that I've lost because of it...

46
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:33,179
I won't change my mind.

47
00:03:33,179 --> 00:03:34,840
You may go now.

48
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:40,539
Director Lin. Please stay.

49
00:03:41,410 --> 00:03:43,120
I'm sorry.

50
00:03:54,690 --> 00:03:59,000
I remember you once said that in business, there are no deals that can't be negotiated.

51
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,940
What's missing is having the right bargaining chips.

52
00:04:00,940 --> 00:04:04,300
Qinghu project may be of little value to you.

53
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:07,689
But for Huateng Land, it is the only way out.

54
00:04:07,689 --> 00:04:11,379
No matter what the conditions are, we will try our best to meet them.

55
00:04:13,020 --> 00:04:17,589
Young man, that's quite some claim. Okay. I'll give you another chance.

56
00:04:19,450 --> 00:04:23,369
I want to see her performance again. Can you make that happen?

57
00:04:23,369 --> 00:04:24,370
[Haicheng Grand Theater, Admission Ticket]

58
00:04:24,370 --> 00:04:26,600
[Mei Han Xiang Ballet Tour]
Ms. Mei Han Xiang?

59
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:29,330
She has retired from the stage for many years.

60
00:04:30,690 --> 00:04:32,250
If you can't do it, don't talk big.

61
00:04:32,250 --> 00:04:35,809
If you can make it happen, you can come to me then.

62
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:46,740
[Dancing Romance]

63
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:49,059
If it weren't for that big box of tickets,

64
00:04:49,060 --> 00:04:52,460
I really thought that Director Lin deliberately tried to make things difficult for us.

65
00:04:53,150 --> 00:04:55,149
He probably really likes her.

66
00:04:55,149 --> 00:04:58,329
The oil painting in his room seems pretty old.

67
00:04:58,330 --> 00:05:03,859
I'm really surprised that someone his age will be a star-struck fan.

68
00:05:03,859 --> 00:05:09,109
We should figure out how to get Ms. Mei to perform again.

69
00:05:11,150 --> 00:05:14,060
Have you watched Ni Ping's show of searching for lost family members, "Waiting For Me"?

70
00:05:14,060 --> 00:05:16,230
We can do that.

71
00:05:16,230 --> 00:05:18,399
Make sure nothing goes wrong with Ms. Mei's interview.

72
00:05:18,399 --> 00:05:20,349
We need to report it after that.

73
00:05:20,349 --> 00:05:21,590
Okay.

74
00:05:22,370 --> 00:05:23,720
My time in the media industry wasn't in vain.

75
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:26,309
I can finally put it to good use. Wait for me.

76
00:05:29,130 --> 00:05:31,089
Excuse me. Could you do me a favor?

77
00:05:31,089 --> 00:05:33,050
- Sorry, we're in a hurry.
- Wait.

78
00:05:33,050 --> 00:05:34,369
We're in the same line of work.

79
00:05:34,369 --> 00:05:36,269
I hope you can take me along to meet Ms. Mei.

80
00:05:36,269 --> 00:05:38,270
I just want to convey a message from an old fan of hers.

81
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:40,059
That's why I can't let you come.

82
00:05:40,060 --> 00:05:42,230
This time, we finally got an exclusive interview with Ms. Mei.

83
00:05:42,230 --> 00:05:43,789
How can I take you with us?

84
00:05:43,789 --> 00:05:45,299
Sorry.

85
00:05:45,299 --> 00:05:47,050
Excuse me.

86
00:05:51,150 --> 00:05:53,789
If it's not convenient for you to take us in,

87
00:05:53,789 --> 00:05:56,010
could you lend us your equipment and credentials?

88
00:05:56,010 --> 00:05:57,690
Are you out of your mind?

89
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:08,940
You may take a break over there.

90
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:13,450
How's that possible?

91
00:06:13,450 --> 00:06:14,909
Do you know them?

92
00:06:14,909 --> 00:06:17,599
Aren't you in the same line of work? Perhaps, they know you.

93
00:06:17,599 --> 00:06:19,060
Come on.

94
00:06:28,150 --> 00:06:29,419
Why are you sitting over here?

95
00:06:29,419 --> 00:06:31,670
Where's our camera?

96
00:06:31,670 --> 00:06:33,740
Where are our credentials?

97
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,550
Su Zhinian.

98
00:06:36,550 --> 00:06:39,009
Have you ever seen a photographer in a suit?

99
00:06:39,009 --> 00:06:41,569
Photographers carry equipment and brave the weather.

100
00:06:41,569 --> 00:06:43,610
None is as smartly dressed as you.

101
00:06:43,610 --> 00:06:44,709
What are you doing?

102
00:06:44,709 --> 00:06:46,689
Remove your coat.

103
00:06:46,689 --> 00:06:48,819
And this too. Untuck your shirt.

104
00:06:48,819 --> 00:06:51,330
The tie. Loosen it.

105
00:06:51,330 --> 00:06:53,529
Hurry. Why are you being shy?

106
00:06:53,529 --> 00:06:54,739
You have to make it look real.

107
00:06:54,739 --> 00:06:56,309
If not, Ms. Mei might see through us, and that will blow our covers.

108
00:06:56,309 --> 00:06:57,710
Did you see two people with a camera?

109
00:06:57,710 --> 00:06:59,139
I think they went that way. Go after them now.

110
00:06:59,139 --> 00:07:01,509
What's going on? They change their minds?

111
00:07:01,509 --> 00:07:04,219
That's right. What if they did? Come on.

112
00:07:04,219 --> 00:07:06,790
How can they do that?

113
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:08,959
Hurry up.

114
00:07:08,959 --> 00:07:10,419
How can you lose your camera?

115
00:07:10,419 --> 00:07:12,960
I have no idea. We have to get it back.

116
00:07:16,260 --> 00:07:20,230
[VIP Lounge]

117
00:07:21,710 --> 00:07:23,520
Hurry.

118
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:32,290
What do we do?

119
00:07:32,290 --> 00:07:34,430
We can't go out now.

120
00:07:34,430 --> 00:07:35,840
This...

121
00:07:36,620 --> 00:07:38,690
This isn't appropriate.

122
00:07:38,690 --> 00:07:41,559
It's okay. They did it willingly.

123
00:07:41,559 --> 00:07:45,230
What matters now is to find Ms. Mei.

124
00:07:45,230 --> 00:07:46,790
You...

125
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,330
What do we do?

126
00:07:53,790 --> 00:07:55,000
Ms. Mei.

127
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,390
Oh my.

128
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:58,960
Who are you?

129
00:08:01,060 --> 00:08:04,159
We're reporters from Haicheng TV Station and we're here to interview you.

130
00:08:04,159 --> 00:08:05,910
Is it?

131
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:12,589
But I seem to remember seeing you two at the hotel lobby yesterday.

132
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:17,329
Indeed, we're not reporters.

133
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:21,729
We took the liberty to see you today because we have a favor to ask of you.

134
00:08:21,729 --> 00:08:25,729
Here's the thing, Ms. Mei. We know an elderly man who's a fan of yours.

135
00:08:25,729 --> 00:08:29,309
He would go to each and every one of your performances.

136
00:08:29,309 --> 00:08:33,799
His greatest wish is to watch you perform again.

137
00:08:33,799 --> 00:08:36,459
I know it's a big ask.

138
00:08:36,459 --> 00:08:39,349
But I hope you'll reconsider it.

139
00:08:39,349 --> 00:08:43,059
Thank him on my behalf. I've retired now.

140
00:08:43,059 --> 00:08:46,710
I won't be performing on stage anymore.

141
00:08:46,710 --> 00:08:48,229
Ms. Mei.

142
00:08:48,229 --> 00:08:50,060
Come on in.

143
00:08:51,180 --> 00:08:53,350
- What's the matter?
- It's them!
- It's them!

144
00:08:53,350 --> 00:08:56,870
It's them. They took our camera and credentials!

145
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:58,709
Didn't they offer them to us?

146
00:08:58,709 --> 00:09:00,559
Here's the thing, Ms. Mei.

147
00:09:00,559 --> 00:09:01,959
These two stole their credentials...

148
00:09:01,959 --> 00:09:05,149
Stole? They disguised as reporters to come in here.

149
00:09:05,149 --> 00:09:08,059
So sorry for the interruption. I'm so sorry.

150
00:09:08,059 --> 00:09:10,560
How is it? Is it broken? You two, please come with me.

151
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,210
It should be fine.

152
00:09:16,490 --> 00:09:17,560
[Dressing Room]

153
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:19,080
Hold on.

154
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:27,280
[Dressing Room]

155
00:09:31,230 --> 00:09:34,080
What's Lin Hansheng's relationship with you?

156
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:48,959
It's almost time. He should be here soon.

157
00:09:48,959 --> 00:09:50,839
Let's get ready.

158
00:09:50,839 --> 00:09:53,610
Okay, I'll step aside.

159
00:09:53,610 --> 00:09:55,109
You can't go.

160
00:09:55,109 --> 00:09:56,319
Why?

161
00:09:56,319 --> 00:09:58,060
How embarrassing it is if you're not here?

162
00:09:58,060 --> 00:10:01,689
What if something unexpected happens? I won't be able to handle it.

163
00:10:01,689 --> 00:10:03,969
Look at you.

164
00:10:03,970 --> 00:10:07,089
Go. Sit at the back. I'll take care of it.

165
00:10:07,089 --> 00:10:08,590
Okay.

166
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,000
Hi.

167
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,800
I'm Wu Gangqiang.

168
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,200
I'm going to the gents.

169
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:30,400
Okay, I'll wait for you.

170
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:43,600
Dr. Yan! Dr. Yan, wait up!

171
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:46,700
Dr. Yan! What's wrong? None is acceptable?

172
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:49,500
That's right. Totally unacceptable!

173
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,400
Stop wasting your time, okay?

174
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,600
I know what you're up to.

175
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:55,400
But there's no need for that and it's impossible.

176
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:57,600
- But...
- But?

177
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:59,400
But what?

178
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:35,100
Hello?

179
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:40,900
Why would a pregnant lady... Cerebral hypoxia and hemorrhage?

180
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:44,000
Which surgeon is in charge?

181
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,000
How are the vital signs?

182
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:49,500
All right. I'll be there in ten.

183
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:52,200
Go home on your own.

184
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:55,800
Dr. Yan, drive safe!

185
00:11:58,100 --> 00:12:00,600
Hi. Is this your friend's wallet?

186
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:02,000
Let me take a look.

187
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:05,000
[Yan Yuan]

188
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,300
That's right. Thank you.

189
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:08,800
You're welcome. It's what we do.

190
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:24,300
Wait for me for three years.

191
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:26,000
I'll cheer on for you alone for the rest of my life.

192
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:29,300
Winter of 1978. Lin Hansheng.

193
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:32,300
When you return, I shall dance for you alone.

194
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:33,700
Waiting for you.

195
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:37,100
Winter of 1978. Mei Hanxiang.

196
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:41,300
I bet Director Lin couldn't forget Ms. Mei.

197
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:43,600
If not, he wouldn't still

198
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:47,600
be keeping this photo and those tickets after so many years.

199
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:55,000
He stayed in Qinghu for five years and didn't leave until 1983.

200
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:58,000
And Ms. Mei left Haicheng in 1981.

201
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,200
After several twists and turns,

202
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:02,400
Ms. Mei went abroad and joined the American Ballet Theater and never came back.

203
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:08,000
Why do you think they couldn't be together?

204
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:13,900
Perhaps, back in those days, they had to yield to circumstances.

205
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:20,400
Director Lin.

206
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,500
Where's the photo?

207
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:26,700
I'm sorry. I accidentally put it inside the file holder.

208
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:35,100
Thank you.

209
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:09,400
Hanxiang.

210
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:13,700
Lin Hansheng.

211
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:18,000
You've aged.

212
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:22,700
That's right.

213
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:25,600
We're not young anymore.

214
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,400
But I don't think I'm old.

215
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:33,000
I said the wrong thing.

216
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,900
You're still so young and beautiful.

217
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:37,800
Look at you.

218
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:40,400
You don't even know how to tell a lie.

219
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:44,600
Why have you lied to me for so many years?

220
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:48,200
I'm sorry.

221
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:50,400
I'm sorry.

222
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:53,800
I waited all these years

223
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:57,800
not to hear you say this.

224
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,000
I...

225
00:15:03,700 --> 00:15:04,700
Han...

226
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:07,300
Stay with Director Lin. I'll go and find Ms. Mei.

227
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:15,100
Actually, it was Ms. Mei who wanted to see you.

228
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:19,400
I think she deliberately set the last stop of the tour

229
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:22,700
in Haicheng just to wait for you.

230
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:32,100
That night, it was my first time going on the stage.

231
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,300
I was so excited.

232
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:40,000
After the performance, I was reluctant to leave.

233
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:44,100
I didn't even get changed and went up on stage again.

234
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:49,300
The stage was completely dark.

235
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:51,800
But I wasn't afraid at all.

236
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:56,600
I kept spinning and dancing

237
00:15:57,500 --> 00:16:02,500
until a beam of light suddenly shone on me.

238
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,800
That year,

239
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:08,600
I was just a poor kid.

240
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:12,000
So poor that I had only a few books with me.

241
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:15,700
To make some pocket money, I went to work at the theater.

242
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:17,700
At first, I just couldn't get it.

243
00:16:17,700 --> 00:16:21,900
With all the dancing and jumping on the stage, what's there really to see?

244
00:16:21,900 --> 00:16:26,000
Until that night, many people came to the show.

245
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:29,400
When the curtain came down, there was loud, thunderous applause.

246
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:33,800
After the show, I was carrying a torchlight and I suddenly came across her.

247
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:38,300
It gave her quite a shock and she fell down.

248
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:44,000
Later on, my foot injury was healed.

249
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,200
But I couldn't fit into my pointe shoes.

250
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:51,200
So he searched all around Haicheng

251
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:53,800
and spent all his money

252
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:58,000
to customize a pair of pointe shoes for me.

253
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,700
He brought it to me

254
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,600
and said...

255
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:07,600
From now on, all your pointe shoes
will be my responsibility.

256
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:11,200
Then, she...

257
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:13,400
pretended to be mad and stared at me.

258
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:15,300
"If I were to dance for a lifetime,"

259
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:17,500
"how long do you think you could take responsibility for me?"

260
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:18,900
He said,

261
00:17:19,660 --> 00:17:21,400
"For a lifetime."

262
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:23,500
But not long after,

263
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:26,600
he was sent to the rural area in Qinghu.

264
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:30,400
In less than a year,

265
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:34,200
he wrote me a letter

266
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:38,700
and told me he had fallen in love with a local girl

267
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:42,100
and that he would marry her at the end of the year.

268
00:17:43,100 --> 00:17:47,900
But as far as I know, Director Lin doesn't have a wife.

269
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:52,800
I only know that later on.

270
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:57,400
If this were to happen in this era,

271
00:17:57,400 --> 00:18:00,000
his lie would have been exposed.

272
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:05,200
But back in those days...

273
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,800
Why did you lie to her back then?

274
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:22,800
[Arrogant Man]

275
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,000
Something happened to me in Qinghu.

276
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:28,600
I thought I would never be able to go back anymore.

277
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:31,300
So you didn't want to waste her time?

278
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:34,000
How should I put it?

279
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,900
Back then,

280
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:39,400
I would do whatever it takes just to come back.

281
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:42,900
As long as there was a chance to perform, I would fight for it.

282
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:45,300
No matter how dangerous the task may be,

283
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:47,400
I would do it.

284
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:49,200
That year, during the winter solstice,

285
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:52,500
I accidentally fell in Qinghu when I was working in the open air.

286
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:54,700
I even broke my leg.

287
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:58,200
It left me with a high fever and pneumonia.

288
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,200
I was bedridden for over half a year.

289
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:04,600
What's more ironic

290
00:19:05,340 --> 00:19:07,379
is that when I was at my lowest,

291
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:09,200
it was Hanxiang's starting point.

292
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,400
My classmates told me

293
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:15,300
that a well-known dance troupe reached out to her.

294
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:18,100
So without hesitation, you lied to her

295
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:20,200
that you fell for someone else.

296
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:25,000
I thought this was the only thing I could do for her.

297
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:27,000
But she isn't married either.

298
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,600
Why didn't you go and see her?

299
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:30,800
You clearly can't get over her.

300
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:40,200
Why is it disconnected at such a critical moment?

301
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:45,000
It's okay.

302
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:50,000
Let bygones be bygones.

303
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,900
Thank you for tonight.

304
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,200
- Doctor.
- Doctor.

305
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:05,500
Doctor, how's my wife?

306
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,900
Don't worry. The baby is safely delivered.

307
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:10,000
What about my wife?

308
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,700
But as for the mother...

309
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:13,800
- How is she?
- We've tried our best.

310
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:16,500
What? Tried your best?

311
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:18,700
Tried your best?

312
00:20:18,700 --> 00:20:19,800
- My daughter!
- Mom.

313
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:21,400
- My daughter!
- Mom!

314
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:22,200
My daughter!

315
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:24,000
Mom! Mom!

316
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:26,800
Mom. Come on.

317
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:34,500
Here.

318
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:38,600
Thank you.

319
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:41,500
Are you okay?

320
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:48,200
Why are you here?

321
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:52,200
You left your wallet in the restaurant.

322
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:59,200
You didn't have to pass it to me today.

323
00:21:00,380 --> 00:21:02,989
It's so late now, and you had to come all the way here.

324
00:21:02,989 --> 00:21:04,300
I'm sorry.

325
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:06,000
It's okay.

326
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:10,000
I saw what happened earlier.

327
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:12,100
Don't beat yourself up.

328
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,900
When I got to the operating theater,

329
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:20,500
she had already given birth.

330
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:22,300
The baby was fine.

331
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:24,900
But she...

332
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,900
I knew I couldn't save her.

333
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:36,700
The only thing I could do was to do my best

334
00:21:38,300 --> 00:21:40,400
to help her live through the day.

335
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:44,600
I don't want that child to spend every birthday

336
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:46,800
with the memory

337
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:50,700
of his mother's death in the future.

338
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:57,000
Dr. Yan. Don't be upset.

339
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,200
I know you've tried your best.

340
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:01,800
You're just a doctor, not a god.

341
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:04,600
You don't have to shoulder all the responsibility.

342
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:07,400
You've done a good job.

343
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,900
Is that really what you think?

344
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,600
You are the gentlest person I have ever met.

345
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:22,900
I guess there are many wonderful memories between you and your mom.

346
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:30,300
It's late. I'm on duty today.

347
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:33,700
Come on. I'll walk you out.

348
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:48,100
She knew it was a misunderstanding.

349
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:50,800
Why does Ms. Mei still refuse to see Director Lin?

350
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,000
Director Lin is to blame too.

351
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:56,400
He knew she was single. But he wouldn't take the initiative.

352
00:22:57,400 --> 00:23:01,800
Does he still feel inferior and worried that he would be a drag on her?

353
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,200
Something like that.

354
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:06,800
Director Lin suffered an illness after he fell into the water.

355
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:08,500
Later on, he found out he had a tumor.

356
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:11,500
He's been going in and out of surgery all these years.

357
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:20,200
So what if I can't get over her?

358
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:22,400
I don't have much time left.

359
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:24,200
Why be a drag on her?

360
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:26,000
[Non-Performing Asset]

361
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:29,800
Is something wrong with your health?

362
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:37,500
I have a favor to ask of you. Don't ever tell her this.

363
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:40,400
It's a tumor.

364
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:44,900
Okay, I give you my word.

365
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:47,400
If I were you,

366
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:50,000
I would make the same choice as well.

367
00:23:51,300 --> 00:23:53,800
He thinks that Ms. Mei belongs to the stage,

368
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:56,700
instead of staying by his side, who's a sick old man.

369
00:23:56,700 --> 00:23:59,400
It's not what he thinks! It's what she thinks!

370
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:02,900
Since they're in love, they should cherish every moment that they get to spend together.

371
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:04,000
Why all the hesitations?

372
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,200
It's not enough for two people to love each other.

373
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:08,800
They have to be responsible for one another.

374
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:13,600
Do men enjoy these false notions of self-sacrifice?

375
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:16,600
Director Lin kept saying that it was for Ms. Mei's sake.

376
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:20,000
If you ask me, the sufferings that she endured for the next few decades were all because of him.

377
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,800
And now, he's doing this.

378
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:24,000
To be blunt, it's just pure selfishness.

379
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:27,300
In the future, if anyone dares to pull this "It's for your own good" on me,

380
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:29,500
I'll tell him to get out of the way!

381
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:34,600
Well, what do you prefer him to do?

382
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:39,400
Obviously, I hope

383
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:45,000
we can rely on each other and have mutual trust.

384
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:48,200
No matter what happens, we'll face it together.

385
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:51,600
Why am I telling you this?

386
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,200
What do you care?

387
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:55,800
That's mine!

388
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:59,000
I'm surprised you have such a high standard.

389
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:02,600
Add another criterion on top of that. Able to ward off evil.

390
00:25:03,300 --> 00:25:04,700
You're so annoying.

391
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:07,300
I'm being serious. Why did you interrupt me?

392
00:25:07,300 --> 00:25:10,100
Whatever it is, I'm telling Ms. Mei about it.

393
00:25:10,100 --> 00:25:12,000
It's up to her to decide.

394
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:14,600
No way. I gave Director Lin my word.

395
00:25:14,600 --> 00:25:18,300
That's right. You did, not me.

396
00:25:25,100 --> 00:25:27,800
I'm going to the washroom. Wait here for me.

397
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:38,200
That's not right. What is she up to again?

398
00:25:50,300 --> 00:25:51,700
Ms. Mei!

399
00:25:55,100 --> 00:25:56,700
Ms. Mei!

400
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:03,000
I was about to find you. Here are the tickets for tomorrow's show.

401
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,800
[Admission Ticket]
You two can come tomorrow.

402
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:06,000
Thank you, Ms. Mei.

403
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:09,300
Ms. Mei. I came to tell you something.

404
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:15,200
Sorry.

405
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:20,200
Okay, thank you.

406
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,600
Director Lin.

407
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,400
Director Lin...

408
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:28,200
From now on, you don't have to tell me about him.

409
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:31,300
Go back and rest. Don't catch a cold.

410
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:35,400
Wait, Ms. Mei. I want to tell you that...

411
00:26:36,770 --> 00:26:38,979
- Qingchun is allergic to pollen.
- I'm not!

412
00:26:38,979 --> 00:26:41,600
It's getting late. Rest earlier.

413
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:44,100
Ms. Mei!

414
00:26:45,100 --> 00:26:47,600
Su Zhinian, I'm not done talking!

415
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:49,800
Why did you drag me here?

416
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:51,500
Su Zhinian!

417
00:26:55,400 --> 00:27:00,400
Su Zhinian. Even if I don't tell Ms. Mei about it, I can make Director Lin come clean with her.

418
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:02,200
Sure.

419
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:05,600
Tomorrow is her official performance. You have until tomorrow.

420
00:27:05,600 --> 00:27:08,100
Okay. I'll take my chances.

421
00:27:08,100 --> 00:27:10,400
Sure. Bring it on.

422
00:28:05,500 --> 00:28:07,000
Speak.

423
00:28:09,800 --> 00:28:11,600
Can't find it?

424
00:28:13,100 --> 00:28:17,200
That means she noticed that something wasn't right.

425
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:21,300
No worries.

426
00:28:22,300 --> 00:28:24,600
Get someone to keep an eye on her and Su Zhinian.

427
00:28:33,700 --> 00:28:35,400
Are you working this weekend?

428
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:37,600
I was recording a domestic violence program in the past two days.

429
00:28:37,600 --> 00:28:39,000
It's a wrap today.

430
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:41,400
I heard that the American Ballet Theater has a tour in Haicheng.

431
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:42,600
My friend gave me two tickets.

432
00:28:42,600 --> 00:28:44,200
Haicheng is my hometown. I'm familiar with the place.

433
00:28:44,200 --> 00:28:47,400
Let's take a trip there and have a short vacation.

434
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:50,450
You still remember that I like to watch ballet performances?

435
00:28:50,450 --> 00:28:51,400
Of course.

436
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:55,900
I remember there's a ballerina by the last name Mei, right?

437
00:28:55,900 --> 00:28:57,200
That's right.

438
00:28:57,200 --> 00:29:01,400
But the one I like is Alina Somova from Russia.

439
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:02,800
Right, she's great too.

440
00:29:02,800 --> 00:29:05,000
Let's watch her performance if there's a chance.

441
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:07,100
-Sure.
- Let's go.

442
00:29:30,600 --> 00:29:32,200
- Director Lin.
- Why are you here?

443
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:35,700
If you're here because of the project, I've notified my staff about it.

444
00:29:35,700 --> 00:29:37,139
Just send your proposal over will do.

445
00:29:37,140 --> 00:29:39,309
No. No. It's Ms. Mei.

446
00:29:39,309 --> 00:29:41,200
Just now, Ms. Mei...

447
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:42,800
What happened to her?

448
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:45,000
Ms. Mei doesn't have a family.

449
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:48,600
She might not have anyone in this lifetime.

450
00:29:48,600 --> 00:29:49,800
Are you willing to take care of her?

451
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:51,800
Wait. Where's she now?

452
00:29:51,800 --> 00:29:55,300
Cut the crap. Tell me where she is. I'll go and find her.

453
00:29:55,300 --> 00:29:57,800
She... She's all right.

454
00:29:57,800 --> 00:30:02,100
I'm sorry, Director Lin. I lied to you.

455
00:30:02,100 --> 00:30:06,100
I just wanted you to get a taste of how Ms. Mei would feel in the future.

456
00:30:06,100 --> 00:30:09,400
You're afraid of not being able to take care of her and that you'll waste her time.

457
00:30:09,400 --> 00:30:13,600
But you never thought about if all she wanted was to find someone who could take care of her,

458
00:30:13,600 --> 00:30:16,200
why stay single until now?

459
00:30:17,700 --> 00:30:19,600
It's true.

460
00:30:19,600 --> 00:30:24,800
Besides love, two people stay together because of their responsibility for one another.

461
00:30:24,800 --> 00:30:28,500
But don't neglect the fact that it's one another.

462
00:30:28,500 --> 00:30:30,800
She, too, wants to be responsible of you.

463
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:36,200
What Ms. Mei wants is someone who can take care of her

464
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:39,000
and is willing to be taken care of by her.

465
00:30:46,580 --> 00:30:50,699
Later, get someone to move the things over there.

466
00:30:50,699 --> 00:30:52,539
- Okay.
- Don't let it get in the way.

467
00:30:52,539 --> 00:30:54,359
- Okay.
- Go ahead.

468
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:58,580
Ms. Mei.

469
00:30:58,580 --> 00:31:03,039
Do you know why Director Lin wants to see you perform again?

470
00:31:04,530 --> 00:31:09,829
It's because he has never come to your show, not once in his life.

471
00:31:09,829 --> 00:31:12,979
But he bought the tickets for all your performances.

472
00:31:12,979 --> 00:31:16,470
But he never stepped inside because of fear

473
00:31:16,470 --> 00:31:18,880
and because he couldn't.

474
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:22,579
All these years, he could only look at the oil painting in his study

475
00:31:22,579 --> 00:31:26,239
of you dancing on the stage when you two first met

476
00:31:26,239 --> 00:31:28,340
to make good on his promise.

477
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:34,320
That's right.

478
00:31:34,320 --> 00:31:36,730
I haven't made good on my promise to him.

479
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:04,919
It's over.

480
00:33:04,919 --> 00:33:06,880
I lost.

481
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:09,160
I guess he's not coming.

482
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:10,720
Let's go.

483
00:35:11,970 --> 00:35:13,690
Hanxiang.

484
00:35:13,690 --> 00:35:15,300
Lin Hansheng.

485
00:35:15,300 --> 00:35:18,999
I owe you a dance, I've made good on my promise.

486
00:35:19,799 --> 00:35:21,370
Perhaps,

487
00:35:22,470 --> 00:35:25,900
it's done between the two of us.

488
00:35:25,900 --> 00:35:27,400
Hanxiang.

489
00:35:29,960 --> 00:35:31,450
I know.

490
00:35:31,450 --> 00:35:37,109
When I was young, I didn't take care of myself and fell ill.

491
00:35:37,109 --> 00:35:39,680
I had surgery last year.

492
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:43,789
Truth be told, I don't know how much time do I have left.

493
00:35:45,880 --> 00:35:48,320
I would like to ask you

494
00:35:48,320 --> 00:35:51,280
if I could use my remaining time

495
00:35:52,630 --> 00:35:55,710
to take care of you and to keep you company?

496
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:46,749
Here, Ms. Mei. Three, two, one.

497
00:36:46,749 --> 00:36:48,870
Cheese!

498
00:36:51,950 --> 00:36:54,050
So this is love.

499
00:36:54,050 --> 00:36:57,049
Didn't you have your heart broken? Do you only know that now?

500
00:36:57,049 --> 00:36:58,610
Shut up, will you?

501
00:37:00,050 --> 00:37:01,990
Ms. Mei. Look.

502
00:37:03,700 --> 00:37:05,790
It's nice, isn't it?

503
00:37:05,790 --> 00:37:08,559
- It's so nice.
- Not bad.

504
00:37:08,559 --> 00:37:10,749
- I'll take a picture for you two.
- It's okay.

505
00:37:10,749 --> 00:37:13,390
- Sure. Thank you.
- Come on.

506
00:37:13,390 --> 00:37:14,700
Come on.

507
00:37:16,170 --> 00:37:18,190
I'll take a picture for you.

508
00:37:19,740 --> 00:37:23,039
All right. One, two, three.

509
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:28,849
- Sir, how much is it?
- 43 yuan.

510
00:37:28,849 --> 00:37:31,600
It's a waste of this last piece of film.

511
00:37:31,600 --> 00:37:33,919
It's all your fault. I look so awful in this!

512
00:37:33,919 --> 00:37:36,659
- Give it to me if you don't like it.
- Why should I?

513
00:37:36,659 --> 00:37:39,280
I paid for the film.

514
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:41,380
So what?

515
00:37:44,860 --> 00:37:46,969
Well, about our bet last night.

516
00:37:46,970 --> 00:37:48,609
How do we go about that?

517
00:37:48,610 --> 00:37:50,770
What do you think?

518
00:37:50,770 --> 00:37:53,089
Ms. Mei stayed because of you.

519
00:37:53,090 --> 00:37:56,050
Director Lin showed up because of me.

520
00:37:56,050 --> 00:37:58,050
